(Please provide the most up-to-date and accurate information for your child(ren) during registration.) From there you will click the link to activate your account. It takes less than a minute.

We are looking forward to a great year!

Reminder!
SJHS Pick up & Drop off Supplies info:
Parents will first need to park in the west parking lot (this is Station 1). Students will enter the building at Door #19 and they will go to their locker where contents are bagged. Pick up your bag and then exit at Door #18. If you have things in the athletic locker rooms you may go and pick them up before exiting the building. (This does not include PE Lockers) After exiting the building students will get back into their parents‚Äô vehicle and go to Station 2 through 5. (Students from the same household can come together, even if last names are in different groups.)

Pete Christy KCBD
April 29 at 11:17 PM ¬∑

The Seminole School Board has voted to name the High School Gymnasium Court after Leland "Buck" Caffey.

Coach Caffey was in Seminole to see this incredible honor.

He won a State basketball championship as a player in 1955 and then was the head basketball coach of the 1979 state basketball championship team.

Coach Caffey definately deserves this.

Video provided by Emily Birdwell of Seminole ISD Communications.

shared_text:
Seminole Texas High School News
February 27 at 3:56 PM ¬∑

Earlier this week SHS Student Council hosted the District Convention in the PAC. There were 14 schools from TASC District 8 present. During this event, the councils met for a day of learning from one another. This years speaker was Kyle Scheele. They also had breakout sessions about StuCo Leadership, Stress Management (led by Mr. Autry), Distracted Driving (led by DPS), Bullying, and Mental Health.

There were 3 District 8 scholarships given out and our very own Madison Dyck was a recipient. Congrats! Lastly, Student Councils were recognized for ALL of their achievements this year. Seminole was recognized as a SWEEPSTAKES school!! SHS StuCo won awards in the following:

--Drug, alcohol, safety and health
--Energy and environment
--Pride and patriotism
--Community Service
--Outstanding Student Council

We are VERY proud of our StuCo and EVERYTHING that they do!

#WeAreSeminole

post_text:
**Edit**

It was not a well head explosion. There was a stuffing box leak which resulted in a release of fluids and H2S.

Greetings SISD families:

Earlier today, Chief of Police Bernie Kraft notified SISD of a well head explosion, due to pressure, just west of Seminole High School. Our High School and F.J. Young campuses immediately went into a Shelter In Place due to the possible presence of H2S gas. The well was quickly and successfully repaired and the shelter in place was released.

Please know that student and staff safety is our highest priority. Thank you for your continued support for our school.

post_text: We could not be more proud of our VASE students and Mr. & Mrs. Autry for their leadership! #WeAreSeminole
shared_text:
Seminole Texas High School News
February 21 at 9:48 PM ¬∑

On Saturday, February 15th, SHS had 54 students enter 63 pieces of art into the Region 17 VASE (Visual Art Scholastic Event) art competition at Plainview High School in Plainview, TX.

The competition consisted of 16 school districts with 21 schools. In the ranking system, a rating of a 4 is the HIGHEST a student can get. Each of those students receive a medal. Seminole High School's students earned 51 total medals. Those receiving the highest ratings are considered to move on to the State Competition.

Out of 393 pieces of art, only 28 were chosen to be state-bound. This is only 7% of the total artwork, 10% of those who earned a medal. Four of our very own SHS students' pieces were chosen to advance to state: Sydney Gonzales (junior), Raven Parker (junior), Sandra Hernandez Tarango (sophomore), and Kevin Ronquillo (freshman).

We are VERY proud of ALL of the students who participated and are extremely excited to showcase them in the Seminole Art Walk in the Powwow Room on March 24th as well as the Night of Fine Arts in the PAC on May 4th.

GO TR1BE! üé®

#WeAreSeminole
